.TH TOUCH 1
.SH NAME
touch \- create empty files or update file timestamps
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B touch
file ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B touch
utility creates the specified files if they do not already exist.

If a file already exists, its modification time is updated.

Multiple files may be specified.

No command-line options are supported.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B touch
utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.
.SH SEE ALSO
cp(1),
rm(1)